text: Abderrahmane Youssoufi ( (); ; 8 March 1924 - 29 May 2020) is a Moroccan politician and human rights activist. He was the Prime Minister of Morocco from 1998 to 2002. He was a human rights lawyer. Youssoufi died of lung cancer on 29 May 2020 at a Casablanca hospital, aged 96.Décès de l’ex-Premier ministre marocain Abderrahman El Youssoufi ==References== Category:1924 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Prime Ministers of Morocco Category:Moroccan lawyers Category:Human rights activists
